@startuml "Executor Module - Strategy Pattern"
title "Executor Module: Command Execution with Strategy Pattern"

' Command Execution
class CommandExecutor {
  + execute(cmd: &str, args: &[String], original_input: Option<&str>): Result<CommandOutput>
  + command_exists(cmd: &str): bool
  + execute_sudo(cmd: &str, args: &[String]): Result<CommandOutput>
  --
  - execute_with_timeout()
  - handle_shell_operators()
  - get_exit_code(status): i32
}

class CommandOutput {
  + stdout: String
  + stderr: String
  + exit_code: i32
  --
  + is_success(): bool
  + combined_output(): String
}

CommandExecutor --> CommandOutput : returns

note top of CommandExecutor
  **Direct Command Execution**
  Simple, composable interface for executing
  shell commands with proper error handling.

  Used directly by orchestrators without
  additional facade abstraction layer.
end note

' Package Manager Strategy Pattern
interface PackageManager <<interface>> {
  + name(): &str
  + is_available(): bool
  + install(package: &str): Result<()>
  + priority(): u8
}

class AptPackageManager {
  + name(): &str
  + is_available(): bool
  + install(package): Result<()>
  + priority(): u8 = 80
}

class YumPackageManager {
  + name(): &str
  + is_available(): bool
  + install(package): Result<()>
  + priority(): u8 = 80
}

class DnfPackageManager {
  + name(): &str
  + is_available(): bool
  + install(package): Result<()>
  + priority(): u8 = 80
}

class PacmanPackageManager {
  + name(): &str
  + is_available(): bool
  + install(package): Result<()>
  + priority(): u8 = 80
}

class BrewPackageManager {
  + name(): &str
  + is_available(): bool
  + install(package): Result<()>
  + priority(): u8 = 90
}

class ChocoPackageManager {
  + name(): &str
  + is_available(): bool
  + install(package): Result<()>
  + priority(): u8 = 70
}

class WingetPackageManager {
  + name(): &str
  + is_available(): bool
  + install(package): Result<()>
  + priority(): u8 = 85
}

AptPackageManager ..|> PackageManager : implements
YumPackageManager ..|> PackageManager : implements
DnfPackageManager ..|> PackageManager : implements
PacmanPackageManager ..|> PackageManager : implements
BrewPackageManager ..|> PackageManager : implements
ChocoPackageManager ..|> PackageManager : implements
WingetPackageManager ..|> PackageManager : implements

' PackageInstaller
class PackageInstaller {
  - package_manager: Box<dyn PackageManager>
  --
  + new(): Self
  + with_package_manager(Box<dyn PackageManager>): Self
  + install_package(name: &str): Result<()>
  + detect_package_manager(): Box<dyn PackageManager>
  + is_available(): bool
  + get_package_manager(): Option<&str>
  --
  # priority_order(): Vec<Box<dyn PackageManager>>
}

PackageInstaller --> PackageManager : selects best via strategy

note top of PackageInstaller
  **Strategy Pattern**
  Selects best PackageManager:

  **Priority Order**
  1. brew (macOS, highest priority=90)
  2. winget (Windows, priority=85)
  3. apt-get (Debian/Ubuntu, priority=80)
  4. dnf (Fedora, priority=80)
  5. yum (RHEL/CentOS, priority=80)
  6. pacman (Arch, priority=80)
  7. choco (Windows fallback, priority=70)

  **Selection Logic**
  - Check is_available() for each
  - Select highest priority match
end note

' Tab Completion
class TabCompletion {
  + get_completions(prefix: &str): Vec<String>
  + complete_commands(prefix): Vec<String>
  + complete_files(prefix): Vec<String>
  + complete_flags(cmd, prefix): Vec<String>
}

TabCompletion --> CommandExecutor : queries available commands

' Package Manager Detection
class PackageManagerDetector {
  + detect_linux(): Option<Box<dyn PackageManager>>
  + detect_macos(): Option<Box<dyn PackageManager>>
  + detect_windows(): Option<Box<dyn PackageManager>>
}

note right of PackageManagerDetector
  **Platform-Specific Detection**
  - Linux: apt, yum, dnf, pacman
  - macOS: brew
  - Windows: winget (preferred), choco
end note

PackageInstaller --> PackageManagerDetector : uses for detection

' Command Cache (from input module)
class CommandCache {
  - available: HashSet<String>
  - unavailable: HashSet<String>
  - aliases: HashMap<String, String>
  --
  + is_available(command: &str): bool
  + clear_cache()
  + load_aliases()
}

CommandExecutor --> CommandCache : uses for fast lookups

note right of CommandCache
  **Lazy Singleton Pattern**
  Thread-safe caching with RwLock:
  - O(1) cache hits
  - O(PATH_length) cache misses
  - Caches both available + unavailable
  - 99% read-heavy workload
end note

' Relationships summary
package "Design Patterns" as Patterns {
  note as PatternNote
    **Strategy Pattern**
    - PackageManager trait
    - 7 implementations for different OSes
    - Selected based on availability and priority

    **Lazy Singleton**
    - CommandCache (global static)
    - Thread-safe with RwLock
    - Lazy initialization

    **Async/Await**
    - All execute methods are async
    - Tokio-based with timeout protection

    **Direct Composition**
    - Orchestrators use CommandExecutor directly
    - No unnecessary abstraction layers
    - Cleaner, more maintainable code
  end note
}

@enduml
